    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="structGEMPIC__Fields_1_1DeRhamField" kindref="compound">DeRhamField</ref></para>
<para>Stores a specific element of a deRham complex</para>
<para><computeroutput>gridType:</computeroutput> Grid::primal or Grid::dual grid</para>
<para><computeroutput>spaceType:</computeroutput> Space::node, Space::edge, Space::face or Space::cell.</para>
<para>spaceType is defined on primal grid: e.g. DeRhamField&lt;dual, node&gt; is the cell based complex dual to DeRhamField&lt;primal, node&gt;</para>
<para>In 1D only Space::node and Space::cell exist.</para>
<para>In 2D there are 4 complexes because of the two different deRham sequences</para>
<para>For node and cell only scalarData will be allocated, for edge and face only vector data </para>
    </detaileddescription>
